## Authentication
<!-- AI: Describe the auth scheme. What header? What token format? How is the token obtained? -->
- All endpoints require: `Authorization: Bearer <token>` unless marked `[public]`
- Token obtained via: `POST /auth/login`
- Token lifetime: <!-- AI: fill, e.g. 24h -->
- On invalid/missing token: return `401 Unauthorized`

## Idempotency
- `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH` endpoints that modify state require an `Idempotency-Key: <uuid>` header.
- Server stores the key for 24 hours and returns the same response for repeated requests.

## Standard error format
```json
{ "error": "machine_readable_code", "message": "Human-readable description." }
```

## Standard error codes
| Code | Meaning | When to use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| 400 | Bad request | Missing field, validation failure |
| 401 | Unauthorized | Missing or invalid token |
| 403 | Forbidden | Token valid but lacks permission |
| 404 | Not found | Resource does not exist |
| 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists, duplicate key |
| 422 | Unprocessable | Input valid but business rule violated |
| 500 | Server error | Unexpected failure — log it, do not expose detail |

